The paper discusses capacity analysis for wireless mobile systems with multiple antenna architectures, which falls under the information theory (cs.IT) sub-category. The analysis considers both transmitter and receiver knowledge of the channel's statistical law, which suggests a possible sub-category of networked systems (cs.NI) or signal processing (cs.SI). The paper specifically focuses on multiple-input multiple-output (MIMO) channels, which is a sub-field of wireless communication and networking (cs.MM). Finally, the paper discusses issues related to capacity-achieving measures, which could fall under the communication complexity (cs.COMM) sub-category.
